The paper deals with optimization algorithms for selecting appropriate drive modes for fuel minimization in plug-in hybrid electric vehicles. This involves integrating trip information and path planning to find an optimal path considering intermediate filling and charging stations. This problem involves decision-making and optimization, which are common themes in the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with path planning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper also involves software engineering aspects, such as developing an online algorithm, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
